Brad Porteus from BSP Construction Consultants started his journey in the construction industry in 1993, leaving University to complete a Plumbing apprenticeship and study Applied Science Construction to gain his Builder Registration. Upon completion of his Plumbing apprenticeship he gained employment as a building supervisor, managing the construction of 1 &amp; 2 storey residential homes for the next 5 years. In 2001, Brad then moved to Indonesia to work as a Project Manager for a Commercial Building Company, building hotel resorts in Bali and Lombok. Upon Brads return to Australia in 2003, he started the Building and Property consulting company known as, BSP Construction Consultants Pty Ltd. The company was run for a small home office in its first couple of years and has now grown into a commercial office with 12 staff and working for clients such as BHP, Leighton Group, Main Roads and the John Holland Group.

